synatx:
  ls [options] [directorys/folders]



  ls : will show all content in dir

  ~ :tilde is use home directory /home/nishant/   use can replace this string with ~

  ls [folder/dir name]  : will show all the content in providec dir. case snsitive names
  ex.  ls Documents/

  pwd :will show u present working directory
  ex. pwd

  clear :will clear the termianl hostroty
  ex. clear

  ls ~ (tilde): will show u home directory content
  ex. ls ~
      ls /home/nishant/

  ls .. : will show u one step back content .means one step back direcotrycontent
  ls ../..  :will show u two step back folder content

  ---------------------------options demo-------------------------------
  
  ls -l  :will show u long forlmate content

  ls -a :will show u hidden files also

  ls -al : u can combine options .this option will show u long as well as hidden content
  ls -la same as above u can use both the way to combime options

  ls -lS : capital S will sort the content on size. Asscending to dessecending

  ls documents/*.txt  : wild card will sort data on extension. this will sort onlys text files present in documents
  ls Documents/*.* :will sort all extention files

  ----------to write ls content to files-------------
  ls -l > out.txt  :this command will write ls command content in out.txt files (>) angule symbol

  ls -d */: will only list all the directorys
  ex. ls -d */ :will show u only directorys

  ----------------------------------MAN ls------------------------------
  man is like directory which show all info for commands
  man ls :ls command info